A High Court sitting in Ado-Ekiti, the Ekiti state capital has sentenced two persons to death by hanging for conspiracy, murder and unlawful possession of human skull. The condemned individuals, Tosin Oluwafemi, 21 and Ogunleye Tajudeen,18, committed the offences according to the charge sheet on February 14, 2017, at Ifaki Ekiti, where they conspired to murder one Joshua Ojo. The offence, according to the charge sheet was contrary to section 516, 316, 319 and section 329(a) of the Criminal Code Cap C16 Laws of Ekiti State 2012. Gunmen abduct police, one other in Abuja Court fixes Dec. 18 to hear N100m suit filed against CCECC… JUST IN: FIRS confirms fire incident at headquarters Lawmaker calls for establishment of Federal Polytechnic in… ALSO READ: Reps decry poor funding of National Women’s Centre Delivering her judgement, Justice Oluwatoyin Abodunde said, “Every evil or good actions in life attracts consequences, in the accused persons’ case, their act has grave consequences. “Therefore, for the offence of conspiracy, the accused persons are sentenced to 7-years-imprisonment and for the second count of murder is sentence to death. “The first and second accused person are hereby sentenced to death by hanging and may the Lord have mercy on your souls.” SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
